                //-----------------------------------------------------------------
                /*DESCRIPTION    : To allow the reordering at the destination each PCIe peer-to-peer request is assigned with PCIe ID noting the source of the request and a sequence number for each request. The target MI-F of each flits is set by this lookup table, the input of the table is {SQN, TargetPCIe_id[3:0]} and the output is the EID of the target. If the PCIe target is in a remote die, the LUT is used and the output of the LUT is the EID of the target MI-F
